{"questionId":"9067561","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Kevlar<sup>®</sup> is used to make racing tires.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/006f2284996bcaa1cfd228e5a75edc448e1508c3.png\" width=\"420\" height=\"124\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Draw the structure of the monomers of Kevlar<sup>®</sup> if the by-product of the condensation polymerization is hydrogen chloride.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/32fc485bcb31248f282a0130307474de90c7fc8b.png\" width=\"184\" height=\"97\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>H<sub>2</sub>NC<sub>6</sub>H<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> ✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2dd3fdcb62e6a712493bae59f284a91bf51e2814.png\" width=\"197\" height=\"149\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>Cl(O)CC<sub>6</sub>H<sub>4</sub>C(O)Cl ✔</span></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067561","referenceCode":"19N.3.hl.TZ0.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw the structure of the monomers of Kevlar® if the by-product of the condensation polymerization is hydrogen chloride.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Options","Options","A: Materials","A.9 Condensation polymers (HL only)","Options","A: Materials","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}